overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application to verify adherence to the Statement of Work and detailed
  questionnaire specifications. The assistant performed an in-depth analysis,
  identifying several critical and important missing features. A structured plan
  was then formulated, outlining specific action items. Over the course of the
  conversation, the assistant systematically implemented all high and medium
  priority tasks. Key achievements include integrating a 1-10 tiredness severity
  scale with safety warnings, implementing detection and recommendations for
  COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, adding a dedicated resources section
  with outbound links, refining EDS scoring with weighted criteria, expanding
  the CSV export to capture all questionnaire data, and incorporating new
  questions for pain, chronic fatigue screening, and medical/mental health
  history. Each change involved updating data types, validation schemas, UI
  components, and report generation logic for both web and PDF formats, ensuring
  a robust and feature-complete application.
